25|$|In 1841, Dorothea Dix {{discovered}} that prison conditions were, <b>in</b> <b>her</b> <b>opinion,</b> inhumane. Prisoners were chained naked, whipped with rods. Others, criminally insane, were caged, or placed in cellars, or closets. She insisted on changes {{throughout the rest}} of her life. While focusing on the insane, her comments also resulted in changes for other inmates.|$|E
